The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Bengal placed in group B
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Bengal placed in group B
            A STAFF REPORTER                      
	Calcutta: Bengal will have to fight it out with Madhya Pradesh, Assam, Vidarbha, Services and Tripura in group B of the Plate Division in next seasons Ranji Trophy.         
	Bengal and Himachal Pradesh were relegated to the Plate Division, while Gujarat and Railways made the Elite Division.         
	According to a BCCI release, the tours and fixtures committee finalised the groupings for the 2008-09 edition.         
	Reigning Ranji Trophy champions Delhi and 37-time winners Mumbai have been pooled together in group A of the Elite Division.         
	THE GROUPINGS         
	Elite Division  Group A: Delhi, Saurashtra, Mumbai, Orissa, Punjab, Hyderabad, Rajasthan and Gujarat; Group B: Uttar Pradesh, Baroda, Andhra Pradesh, Karnataka, Maharashtra, Tamil Nadu and Railways.         
	Plate Division  Group A: Kerala, Haryana, Himachal Pradesh, Goa, Jammu and Kashmir and Jharkhand; Group B: Bengal, Madhya Pradesh, Assam, Vidarbha, Services and Tripura.                                                                                                                          
